reviewText: Had there been SDH or CC, I would have enjoyed this collection immensely.Being near deaf I had to jack the volume up to distortion levels to hear much of it.Possibly an issue with the audio mastering as well.Still a better value than trying to hunt down these cult classics individually.
summary: Entertaining collection, decent value, no Closed Captions

Title: Cops And Robbersons/Leonard Part 6/What Planet Are You From/Vibes

reviewText: Cops and Robbersons is a wonderful showcase for Jack Palance, with Chevy Chase doing his usual putz schtick. Leonard Part 6 was an abomination--just amazingly bad, with no idea what it was doing or what audience it was targeting. What Planet Are You from is a bad Rom Com with a sci-fi skin on it--again, I have no idea what their target audience might have been. And the prize of the set if Vibes. You can buy Vibes on it's own for $75-125, or buy this set and ignore the other three movies for $7. Your choice. Just be aware that nothing else in this set is worth watching more than once.
summary: One and a half good movies
Title: Cops And Robbersons/Leonard Part 6/What Planet Are You From/Vibes

reviewText: I've always had a soft spot for Vibes.  Cindy Lauper is sweet and goofy, the story is interesting, Peter Falk is great, Jeff Goldbloom is Cindy's romantic interest, the Peruvian scenery is great, Cindy's end song is very nice, and the bad guys get their just desserts in the end.  I watched Leonard Part 6 once.  Can't remember much about it and am unlikely to watch it again.  I remember the leads in Cops and Robbersons from seeing it years ago, Chevy Chase and Jack Palance, and they were fun.  Eventually I'll watch it again, but not now.
summary: Cops & Robbersons i Watchable, Leonard is Not, And I Always Liked Vibes
